\stopplacetable

Annotations can be achieved with different approaches. We present here the
\type{\mathannotation} method.

\startbuffer
\startformula
  \mathannotation[bottom={= mx}]
  {\underbrace{x + x + \ldots + x}} +
  \mathannotation[bottom={= ny}]
  {\underbrace{y + y + \ldots + y}}
  = mx + ny
\stopformula
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer

\getbuffer

\stopsubsection

\page[bigpreference]

\startsubsection[title=Big operators]

In \CONTEXT\ there are four groups of predefined big operators: integrals,
summations, products and operators. They can be setup with

\shortsetup{setupmathoperators}

There is a big group of different integrals. One needs however to pay attention,
that not all of them are available in all fonts. The summations group contain
three predefined signs and the product group contains two signs. The operators
group contains 21 different symbols.

Here follow some examples

\startbuffer[Operators]
\m{ \int_0^1 f(x) \dd x \neq \sum_{k=1}^n a_k \neq
    \prod_{k=1}^n a_k \neq \bigoplus_{k=1}^n a_k} \crlf
\dm{\int_0^1 f(x) \dd x \neq \sum_{k=1}^n a_k \neq
    \prod_{k=1}^n a_k \neq \bigoplus_{k=1}^n a_k}
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer[Operators]

\getbuffer[Operators]

As you can see the limits in displayed math are to the right of the integral. One
can change this by

\startbuffer
\setupmathoperators
  [integrals]
  [method=auto]
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer

\page[bigpreference]

\start
  \getbuffer

  Then the above example looks like this

  \getbuffer[Operators]
\stop

\stopsubsection

\startsubsection[title=Radicals]

Radicals in math are obtained with the commands \type{\sqrt} or \type{\root}.
These can have an argument if the root is not a square root. Another way of
representing a (square) root is rising the expression to the power of the
fraction:

\startbuffer
\startformula
  \sqrt{1 + x} = (1 + x)^{\frac{1}{2}} \breakhere
  \root[n=n]{1 + x} = \root[n]{1 + x} = \sqrt[n]{1 + x} = (1+x)^{\strut 1/n}
\stopformula
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer

\getbuffer

Radicals can have different appearances which can be influenced with

\shortsetup{setupmathradical}

\stopsubsection

\startsubsection[title=Text]

In case there should appear normal text inside a math-formula the command
\type{\mtext} is used:

\startbuffer
\startformula
  \mtext{Like this: } a^2 + b^2 = c^2 \breakhere
  n = \underbrace{1 + 1 + \ldots + 1}_{n \mtext{ terms}}
\stopformula
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer

\getbuffer

There is also \type{\texthere} which is used as follows

\startbuffer
\startformula
  1 + 2 - 3
  \breakhere
  \texthere[left]{and}
  4 + 5 + 6 =  7 + 8
\stopformula
\stopbuffer

\typebuffer

\getbuffer

\stopsubsection

\doifmode{Book}{\page[yes]}

